<h1>Maximum downslope elevation change</h1>

<p>This tool calculates the maximum elevation drop between each grid cell and
its neighbouring cells. The user must specify the name of the input digital
elevation model (DEM) and the output raster name. <b><i>NoData </i></b>valued grid cells
in the input pointer image will be assigned <b><i>NoData</i></b> values in the
output image. The output raster is of the <i>float</i> data type and
<i>continuous</i> data scale.</p>
<br>


